<paragraph id="8B82EE275F42FFA5FF2674C118104098" blockId="2.[151,401,691,750]" box="[151,336,726,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
(
<figureCitation id="1306F2A25F42FFA5FF2E74C118434098" box="[159,259,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[207,1362,1183,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1428,1169,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov. 1 – 3: (1) habitus (dorsolateral view); (2) head and thorax (dorsal); (3) head (ventral). Habralebra gillettei Young 4 – 6: (4) habitus (dorsolateral view); (5) head and thorax (dorsal); (6) head (ventral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283590/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Figs 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FF6674C119A24098" box="[215,226,726,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
–3
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1306F2A25F42FFA5FEBE74C118094098" box="[271,329,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1419,1442]" captionTargetBox="[285,1286,180,1390]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[279,1308,133,1405]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 15. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov.: (7) forewing; (8) hind wing; (9) abdominal apodeme (ventral); (10) pygofer (lateral); (11) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (12) style (ventral); (13) style (lateral); (14) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (15) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283591/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
7– 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FE9F74C118094098" box="[302,329,726,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B82EE275F42FFA5FF26750918784108" blockId="2.[151,1436,798,1116]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Total length 
<quantity id="4CC543C25F42FFA5FE93750918EC4140" box="[290,428,798,822]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.6">2.6–2.8 mm</quantity>
. General color beige, eyes brown. Crown with anterior margin slightly projected medially; ocelli pale-yellow; pronotum approximately 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FD2375551BF5412C" box="[658,693,834,858]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times longer than crown, margin of laterobasal angles exceeding width of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B82EE275F42FFA5FF76759D1A844667" blockId="2.[151,1436,798,1116]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Forewing (
<figureCitation id="1306F2A25F42FFA5FEF0759D18C741D4" box="[321,391,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[207,1362,1183,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1428,1169,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov. 1 – 3: (1) habitus (dorsolateral view); (2) head and thorax (dorsal); (3) head (ventral). Habralebra gillettei Young 4 – 6: (4) habitus (dorsolateral view); (5) head and thorax (dorsal); (6) head (ventral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283590/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1306F2A25F42FFA5FE27759D18E541D4" box="[406,421,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1419,1442]" captionTargetBox="[285,1286,180,1390]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[279,1308,133,1405]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 15. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov.: (7) forewing; (8) hind wing; (9) abdominal apodeme (ventral); (10) pygofer (lateral); (11) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (12) style (ventral); (13) style (lateral); (14) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (15) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283591/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">7</figureCitation>
) pale-yellow to white-milky; apical region of cell cup with light-brown spot; apical region of cells c, r, m, cua, and central region of apical cells irregularly yellowish-brown. 
<collectingCountry id="F32AAEB75F42FFA5FBF975B91DC041B0" box="[1096,1152,942,966]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing (
<figureCitation id="1306F2A25F42FFA5FB6075B91C5541B0" box="[1233,1301,942,966]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1419,1442]" captionTargetBox="[285,1286,180,1390]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[279,1308,133,1405]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 15. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov.: (7) forewing; (8) hind wing; (9) abdominal apodeme (ventral); (10) pygofer (lateral); (11) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (12) style (ventral); (13) style (lateral); (14) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (15) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283591/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FAB675B91C5541B0" box="[1287,1301,942,966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) with veins AA and AP 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FE9075F518694186" box="[289,297,994,1008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="1.0">1</number>
not fused in apical half; vein CuA 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FD7775F51B8E4186" box="[710,718,994,1008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
free from point basad of vein MP 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FBD475F51D2D4186" box="[1125,1133,994,1008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
; vein CuP confluent with submarginal vein, basad of vein MP 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FD9A721F1B734660" box="[555,563,1032,1046]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="2.0">2</number>
, approximately on wing midlength.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B82EE275F42FFA5FF7672371831462A" blockId="2.[151,1436,798,1116]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Abdominal apodeme (
<figureCitation id="1306F2A25F42FFA5FE7D72371B55464E" box="[460,533,1056,1080]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1419,1442]" captionTargetBox="[285,1286,180,1390]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[279,1308,133,1405]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 15. Balera fiuzai, sp. nov.: (7) forewing; (8) hind wing; (9) abdominal apodeme (ventral); (10) pygofer (lateral); (11) subgenital plate (lateroventral); (12) style (ventral); (13) style (lateral); (14) aedeagus and connective (ventral); (15) aedeagus (lateral)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283591/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF5FC005F42FFA5FDB772371B55464E" box="[518,533,1056,1080]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) long, reaching sixth segment; apex truncated, slightly concave with lateral external projection.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF42BEAF5F42FFA5FF2671461C4545F0" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283590/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" targetBox="[207,1362,1183,1817]" targetPageId="2">
