<subSubSection id="C327BDAC5F44FFA3FF7676801BAA436A" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B82EE275F44FFA3FF7676801BAA436A" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94932355F44FFA3FF767680180F42C6" bold="true" box="[199,335,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3D95A45F44FFA3FEE9768F18AB42C6" box="[344,491,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiuzai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94932355F44FFA3FEE9768F18AB42C6" box="[344,491,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Balera fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94932355F44FFA3FE45768F1B1042C6" bold="true" box="[500,592,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A8F4E5F44FFA3FE45768F1B1042C6" box="[500,592,152,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the pygofer, style and aedeagus, the last very superficially, similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D95A45F44FFA3FEB176AA189242A3" authority="Freytag" authorityName="Freytag" box="[256,466,189,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myersi">
<emphasis id="B94932355F44FFA3FEB176AA182F42A2" box="[256,367,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">B. myersi</emphasis>
Freytag
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from that species by the larger size of the posterodorsal projection of the pygofer, the narrower aedeagal atrial region and sinuate stem (in lateral view), and the number and position of aedeagal apical processes (Freytag 
<number id="3DF5FC005F44FFA3FD1077131B9D436A" box="[673,733,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" value="1992.0">1992</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C327BDAC5F44FFA3FF76773F1C634312" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B82EE275F44FFA3FF76773F1C634312" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94932355F44FFA3FF76773F180E4336" bold="true" box="[199,334,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of Prof. Paulo Sérgio Fiuza Ferreira, PhD. (Departamento de Biologia Animal da Universidade Federal de Viçosa), in recognition of his contributions to entomology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
